12 receiving notice of certification.
13 B. If the rural fund does not receive the cash investment and
14 issue the capital investment within such time period following
15 receipt of the certificate notice, the certification shall lapse and
16 the rural fund shall not issue the capital investment without
17 reapplying to the Department for certification. Lapsed
18 certifications shall revert to the Department and shall be reissued
19 pro rata to applicants whose capital investment allocations were
20 reduced in accordance with the application process provided under
21 subsection D of Section 3 of this act.
22 C. A rural fund, before making a qualified investment, may
23 request from the Department a written opinion as to whether the
24 business in which it proposes to invest is an eligible business.
